The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Mittal takes $50-bn hit
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                       Mittal takes $50-bn hit
                              Mittal: Tough times                            
	London, Nov. 2 (PTI): Steel tycoon Lakshmi N. Mittal has lost $50 billion because of the global financial crisis.        
	The losses are in ArcelorMittal, in which Mittal and his family members hold a 43.02 per cent stake.        
	Shares of the worlds No. 1 steel company had bucked the trend in the US and the Europe, where the markets had started their downslide way back in August-September last year.        
	ArcelorMittal continued to gain value till about five months ago, and its share price scaled an all-time high of $104.77 on June 5 on the US bourses.        
	The company then got mauled on the bourses, with the scrip recently falling to $25-levels.         
	During these five months, market capitalisation had plummeted to $37.3 billion from a high of over $150 billion.         
	The value of Mittals holdings fell to $16 billion from $66 billion on June 5.        
	According to the companys latest shareholding data, the Mittal family owns 623.285 million shares, while the rest is public holding and treasury shares.        
	The value of non-promoter shares has also plunged sharply from about $85 billion to about $20 billion.                                                                                                                                      
